==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Meadowwort
<hw>Mead"ow*wort`</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The name of
several plants of the genus <gen>Spiraea</gen>, especially the white- or
pink-flowered <spn>Spiraea salicifolia</spn>, a low European and
American shrub, and the herbaceous <spn>Spiraea Ulmaria</spn>, which has
fragrant white flowers in compound cymes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Meadowy</ent>⟦br⟧
